    "epitet": "Merciful Death",
    "description": "Princess of Hel, the realm of the dead. Dearly loves her mother, Hel, who rules it. She finds Hel's increasing mercilessness toward the living disquieting.",
    "artist": "Kozaki Yusuke (コザキユースケ)",
    "voiceActorEN": "Xanthe Huynh",
    "voiceActorJP": "雨宮天",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I am Eir of the realm of the dead. But now, I have become your prisoner— haven't I?",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "This world is dazzling...the people, the trees, even the wind. The light of life is so...so...abundant.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Hel, the realm of the dead... I lived there so long with only my mother.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "If you are tired, I'll help you sleep. Just for the night—not forever.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Imagine that your body is ravaged by incurable disease or wracked with pain that never ceases... You'd consider death a kindness then.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "My blade, Lyfja, offers death to those who seek it. To those who wish to live, it offers compassion instead.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I am Eir, daughter of the sovereign of death. Do not worry. I seek only friendship—not your life.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "Strength wells up within me...",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Life is growth... I am no exception.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "No, no—I am not performing as I should. I apologize.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Thank you. I see it so clearly now— your kindness makes me feel such happiness.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "Ah, <Player Name>... I apologize if I look gloomy to you. I am not used to smiling. Did I smile as a child? I can't quite recall... My memories are so fuzzy, so faint... I remember giving Mother a flower. She smiled, and I was so happy. I am still that child. I would still love to make someone happy like I did then. Maybe...if I can bring you a little joy, my life would have some value to it. Please, tell me what I can do. If I could help, I'd be happy. I'd have accomplished something, at least.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
